{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 16,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Corinthians 16 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:1",
      "text": "Now concerning the contribution for the saints: as I directed the churches of Galatia, so you also are to do.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:2",
      "text": "On the first day of every week, each of you is to put something aside and store it up, as he may prosper, so that contributions need not be made when I come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:3",
      "text": "And when I arrive, I will send those whom you accredit by letter to carry your gift to Jerusalem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:4",
      "text": "If it seems advisable that I should go also, they will accompany me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:5",
      "text": "I will visit you after passing through Macedonia, for I intend to pass through Macedonia,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:6",
      "text": "and perhaps I will stay with you or even spend the winter, so that you may speed me on my journey, wherever I go.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:7",
      "text": "For I do not want to see you now just in passing; I hope to spend some time with you, if the Lord permits.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:8",
      "text": "But I will stay in Ephesus until Pentecost,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:9",
      "text": "for a wide door for effective work has opened to me, and there are many adversaries.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:10",
      "text": "When Timothy comes, see that you put him at ease among you, for he is doing the work of the Lord, as I am.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:11",
      "text": "So let no one despise him. Speed him on his way in peace, that he may return to me; for I am expecting him with the brethren.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:12",
      "text": "As for our brother Apollos, I strongly urged him to visit you with the other brethren, but it was not at all his will to come now. He will come when he has opportunity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:13",
      "text": "Be watchful, stand firm in your faith, be courageous, be strong.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:14",
      "text": "Let all that you do be done in love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:15",
      "text": "Now, brethren, you know that the household of Stephanas were the first converts in Achaia, and they have devoted themselves to the service of the saints;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:16",
      "text": "I urge you to be subject to such men and to every fellow worker and laborer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:17",
      "text": "I rejoice at the coming of Stephanas and Fortunatus and Achaicus, because they have made up for your absence;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:18",
      "text": "for they refreshed my spirit as well as yours. Give recognition to such men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:19",
      "text": "The churches of Asia send greetings. Aquila and Prisca, together with the church in their house, send you hearty greetings in the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:20",
      "text": "All the brethren send greetings. Greet one another with a holy kiss.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:21",
      "text": "I, Paul, write this greeting with my own hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:22",
      "text": "If any one has no love for the Lord, let him be accursed. Our Lord, come!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:23",
      "text": "The grace of the Lord Jesus be with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-corinthians.16.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 16:24",
      "text": "My love be with you all in Christ Jesus. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
